<h4>Shrinking the Family</h4>

<p>All this would naturally leave us expecting to find one net addition - namely Richard [I] - to the Noonan household by
    the time of the next census on 2 April 1871, whatever address (on or near Whit Lane presumably) we would find they were
    living at by that date. And yes, Richard was there as expected, but the overall size of the household hadn&#39;t changed since 1861,
    because there was no sign of any Margaret or Mary Ann. For a long time - before we learned that her real name was Mary Ann - we scoured the local
    lodging houses for a young Margaret Noonan, who we assumed would have left home to become an independent working woman. But
    there were large question marks around all the possible candidates we discovered, and when we eventually learned her true name,
    it did not take too long to discover the unexpected (to us at least) loss that the family had suffered.</p>
