<br>
<u>An Industrial Accident</u>
<br>


<p style="margin-top: 0;">We have no more news or sightings of the family until 1874, but then suddenly they are smitten by
    a truly horrifying and devastating event. It seems that, unlike his older brother, John had left school fairly early to work in the satanic
    mills. It hadn't been unknown for children to start work in the mills as young as eight, but by the 1870s this
    would have seemed extreme. More likely he left school at age twelve, or perhaps even fourteen. The latter possibility stands out, as
    his inexperience would place him at greater risk of an accident. Maybe, unlike James, he was not academically inclined, and
    gung-ho to get out into the world and earn. Maybe a little too gung-ho. Whatever, let's allow the press and the authorities
    to relate the dreadful facts barely.</p>
