<p style="clear:both">The sequence of events was as follows: the tragedy occurred early (still bleary-eyed with sleep?) on the morning of Wednesday
    25 February. The coroner, a Fred Price, held his inquest on the Thursday, recording a verdict of accidental death. From information
    provided by Salford Bereavement Services in October 2018, a grave at Weaste was purchased in the name of John Noonan (address 65 Whit
    Lane) on the Friday. Presumably a headstone was also purchased on the same day, and an inscription commissioned, for on Saturday 28
    February 1874 - the day the weekly Salford Chronicle was published - John junior was interred at Grave No. 2447, Plot C20 at Weaste
    cemetery, and here is the headstone, 144 years later, photographed in September 2018.</p>

